Symbolic Map Matching
Copy
<div>  
  Mapping is the process of creating a visual representation of an area, illustrating spatial relationships between features, whether geographical, data-driven, or conceptual. It involves gathering data through surveys, satellite imagery, or, in the case of medieval T-O maps, symbolic, circular representations of the world. A T-O map (or Orbis Terrarum) is a medieval world map representing the physical world as a circle divided into three parts by a "T" shape.  
</div>  

<div>  
  <span>This example of a T-O map:</span>  
  <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Hereford_mappa_mundi.jpg/400px-Hereford_mappa_mundi.jpg" alt="T-O Map Example" loading="lazy">  
</div>  

<div>  
  Instructions: Drag and drop the following locations with their reference photos. Once all of the matches have been completed, thank you for playingâ€”and consider the items in the Tâ€‘O maps and their placement, as compared to the photo references.  
</div>  

